						<div class="col-lg-6 insurence-left">
							<h1>Maha Shivaratri</h1>
							<p style="text-align:justify;color:#000">
							The Shivaratri Festival honours the Hindu Lord Shiva and is normally held in February/March. 
							Devout Hindus worship at Shiva temples, but around the country (especially in predominantly Hindu areas) an 'air' of festivity can be found, as it's the one day of the year when cannabis is not illegal in Nepal (due to religious reasons).
							 Thousands of sadhus (Hindu holy men) converge at the Pashupatinath Temple in Kathmandu to celebrate Shivaratri.</p>
							<div class="list-wrap">
								<ul>
									<li>Festival of Lord Shiva</li>
									<li>Festival for the Sadhus(Hindu Holy men) especially </li>		
									<li>Venue: All over Nepal having Lord Shiva's Temple</li>
									<li>If you are in central, Pashupatinath Temple is the one you can visit and enjoy at.</li>
									<li>Held: February/March</li>
									<li>Durations: 1 day only </li>
								</ul>
							</div>
						</div>
						<div class="col-lg-6 insurence-right">
